headline: In These Suburbs, Long Lines Meant Good News for the President
text: UPPER ARLINGTON, Ohio — In an affluent pocket of Upper Arlington, a suburb of Columbus, dozens of voters, masked and socially distanced, spanned the length of Jones Middle School and the block behind it by the time the polling place opened Tuesday morning.
snippet: President Trump is counting on strong turnout in staunchly Republican neighborhoods to counter growing Democratic support in the suburbs.
